<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5738&amp;p=52654#p52654"><![CDATA[
I wouldn't go to Famicomworld for any info... Besides, most of the amp circuits out there aren't designed properly for the job.<br /><br /><img src="http://img213.imageshack.us/img213/7609/circuit.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br />You can use any general purpose PNP transistor. <br /><br />You should definitely remove the RF modulator if it's still present so it doesn't affect the mod.<br /><br />For audio connect the positive leg of a 10uF capacitor to the cartridge connector pin 46, and the negative leg to your audio output. I'm not sure what the level is/if it also should be buffered but that's a better start.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=20">kyuusaku</a> — Sun Nov 15, 2009 12:15 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
